
---


@startuml

' Classes
class Resident {
    +String name
    +String streetAddress
    +String phoneNumber
    +String email (optional)
    +List<Item> itemsToPickup
    +Date pickupDate
}

class PickupRequest {
    +Resident resident
    +Date scheduledDate
    +TimeWindow timeWindow
    +List<Item> items
    +String status
}

class Item {
    +String description
    +double weight
    +double dimensions
    +Category category
}

class Category {
    +int id
    +String name
}

class VolunteerDriver {
    +String name
    +String contactInfo
    +Set<DayOfWeek> availableDays
}

class Vehicle {
    +String licensePlate
    +double maxStorageCapacity
    +VolunteerDriver assignedDriver
    +List<PickupRequest> scheduledPickups
}

class PickupRoute {
    +Vehicle vehicle
    +List<Location> route
    +Date date
    +Time startTime
    +Time endTime
}

class Location {
    +String address
    +double latitude
    +double longitude
}

class DistributionCenter {
    +String name
    +Location location
    +List<Article> receivedArticles
    +Employee manager
}

class Employee {
    +String name
    +String role
    +DistributionCenter assignedCenter
}

class Article {
    +Item item
    +String RFIDTag
    +String qualityStatus
    +Category category
}

class FoodBank {
    +String name
    +Location location
}

class Client {
    +String name
    +String homeAddress
    +Set<Category> interestedCategories
    +List<Article> requestedArticles
}

class DeliveryRequest {
    +Client client
    +Article article
    +Date scheduledDeliveryDate
    +VolunteerDriver assignedDriver
}

' Relationships
Resident "1" -- "0..*" PickupRequest : places
PickupRequest "1" -- "1" Item : includes
PickupRequest "1" -- "1" TimeWindow : has
PickupRequest "1" -- "1" Location : at
PickupRequest "1" -- "1" PickupRoute : part of
PickupRoute "1" -- "1" Vehicle : assigned to
Vehicle "1" -- "1" VolunteerDriver : driven by
VolunteerDriver "1" -- "0..*" DayOfWeek : available on
PickupRoute "1" -- "0..*" PickupRequest : contains
Item "1" -- "1" Category : belongs to
Article "1" -- "1" Item : represents
Article "1" -- "1" Category : categorized as
Article "1" -- "1" DistributionCenter : delivered to
Client "1" -- "0..*" Category : interested in
Client "1" -- "0..*" DeliveryRequest : requests
DeliveryRequest "1" -- "1" VolunteerDriver : handled by
DeliveryRequest "1" -- "1" Article : delivers
DistributionCenter "1" -- "1" Employee : managed by
PickupRequest "1" -- "1" Resident : from
PickupRequest "1" -- "1" PickupRoute : added to

note right of DistributionCenter
    In some cities, H2S offers
    delivery services to clients.
end note

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Entities:

- **Resident**: Submits a pickup request with personal info and item descriptions.
- **PickupRequest**: A request made by a resident to have items picked up.
- **Item & Category**: Represents donated items and their classifications.
- **VolunteerDriver & Vehicle**: Volunteers who drive pickup/delivery vehicles.
- **PickupRoute**: Daily schedule for a volunteer driver's pickups.
- **DistributionCenter**: Where articles are sorted, tagged, and cataloged.
- **FoodBank**: Direct drop-off point for non-perishable food items.
- **Client & DeliveryRequest**: For clients who need assistance receiving articles via delivery.

---

### 💡 Notes:
- The diagram supports both **pickup** and **delivery** operations.
- The **category list** is standardized with 134 categories.
- Only **second-hand articles** go through the distribution center; **food items** are sent directly to the food bank.
- Some cities offer **delivery service**, which is modeled separately.

